  ;; --- COMPONENT PLACEMENT & WIRING NOTES ---
  (text "=== UPPER PCB  rev 1.2  ===\n\nJ5: FPC 6-pin 0.5mm top-contact connector\n     Center-bottom of board (Y=+15mm from center)\n     Pin1->3V3, Pin2->GND\n     Pin3->BTN_LEFT, Pin4->BTN_RIGHT\n     Pin5->BTN_BACK, Pin6->BTN_FWD\n\nSW4: Kailh 6x6x9.5mm upright through-hole (Left click)\n     Position: X=-10mm, Y=-12mm from board center\n     Plunger faces UP (+Z) -- pressed by left rocker button\n     Pin pair A -> GND\n     Pin pair B -> R1 -> BTN_LEFT (FPC Pin 3)\n\nSW5: Kailh 6x6x9.5mm upright through-hole (Right click)\n     Position: X=+10mm, Y=-12mm from board center\n     Plunger faces UP (+Z) -- pressed by right rocker button\n     Pin pair A -> GND\n     Pin pair B -> R2 -> BTN_RIGHT (FPC Pin 4)\n\nSW6: Kailh 6x6x9.5mm side-mount through-hole (Back)\n     Position: X=-24mm, Y=0 (left board edge)\n     Plunger faces LEFT (outward) through top_frame wall cutout\n     Pin pair A -> GND\n     Pin pair B -> R3 -> BTN_BACK (FPC Pin 5)\n\nSW7: Kailh 6x6x9.5mm side-mount through-hole (Forward)\n     Position: X=+24mm, Y=0 (right board edge)\n     Plunger faces RIGHT (outward) through top_frame wall cutout\n     Pin pair A -> GND\n     Pin pair B -> R4 -> BTN_FWD (FPC Pin 6)\n\nR1: 10k 0402 pull-up  3V3 -> BTN_LEFT\n     Between SW4 signal pin and 3V3 rail\nR2: 10k 0402 pull-up  3V3 -> BTN_RIGHT\n     Between SW5 signal pin and 3V3 rail\nR3: 10k 0402 pull-up  3V3 -> BTN_BACK\n     Between SW6 signal pin and 3V3 rail\nR4: 10k 0402 pull-up  3V3 -> BTN_FWD\n     Between SW7 signal pin and 3V3 rail\n\nC1: 100nF 0402 decoupling cap\n     Between 3V3 rail and GND, near J5\n\nH1: M2 mount hole at X=-15mm, Y=0 (matches top_frame post)\nH2: M2 mount hole at X=+15mm, Y=0 (matches top_frame post)\n\nNOTE: GND is a shared pour on both layers.\nNOTE: All switches active-LOW. Signal reads 3V3 when open, 0V when pressed.\nNOTE: Remove R_PU1-R_PU4 from lower PCB -- pull-ups now live here."
    (at 30 90 0)
    (uuid "00000002-0001-0001-0001-000000000099")
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left))
  )
